org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api

Interface ChronoDBInternal.ChronoReturningJob<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of this job.
    Enclosing interface:
    ChronoDBInternal
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface ChronoDBInternal.ChronoReturningJob<T>
    A functional interface that represents a job to be executed on a ChronoDB or one of its components.

    This variant of the interface specifies the execute() method including a return type. There is also ChronoDBInternal.ChronoNonReturningJob which features an execute() method that returns void.

    It is recommended to implement this interface using Java Lambda Expressions.
